Airway dilation can be performed using a variety of tools and may be an adjunct to performing stenting. 29 CPT code 31630 does not specify balloon dilation, so no difference exists between rigid or /uniFB02 exible dilation of an airway stenosis or stricture with a balloon, rigid bronchoscope, any bougie, or dilator.
CPT ¼ Current Procedural Terminology; PDT ¼ photodynamic therapy; wRVU ¼ work relative value unit.
